==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Noggin
<hw>Nog"gin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Ir.
<ets>noigin</ets>, or Gael. <ets>noigean</ets>. Cf. 1st
<er>Nog</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small mug or cup.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A measure equivalent to a gill.</def>
<specif>Hence:</specif> <def>a small quantity of a beverage.</def>
<mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The head (of a person).</def>
<mark>[slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> noodle, noddle.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nogging</ent>⟦br⟧
